[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

With 5 cards in the "other" Major and a 5-card Minor suit this looks like an ideal Michaels Cue-Bid, right? No, not really. While it would not be a capital offense to bid 2\H here, it generally works out better with 13-16 point hands to just overcall in your higher-ranking suit. You bid 1\S. Partner responds 2\H.  

Partner's cue-bid shows a limit-raise or better in \Ss. So you bid 4\S without the blink of an eye.}

[Event ""]
